-- Vivendi 2006 net adjusted profit meets target
-- 
-- Wed Mar 7, 2007 2:21am EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/03/07/us-vivendi-results-idUSPAC00779320070307

 

 PARIS  (Reuters) - French media and telecoms group Vivendi ( VIV.PA ) posted on Wednesday an 18 percent rise in adjusted full-year net profit in line with forecasts, pulled by Maroc Telecom and its games, French mobile and pay-TV units. 


 The group made a full-year net adjusted profit of 2.614 billion euros ($3.43 billion) compared with expectations of 2.615 billion euros, based on a Reuters poll of 10 analysts. It rose from 2.218 billion euros in 2005. Vivendi also raised its dividend 20 percent to 1.20 euros a share for the year 2006. The group confirmed its 2007 and 2011 target of adjusted net profit of at least 2.7 billion euros and between 3.5 billion and 4 billion euros respectively.